components.name: Fetch AirVisual Data
components.description: Fetches current air quality and weather data from the AirVisual API, saves it as a JSON file, and performs duplicate detection to skip processing if data already exists.

components.name: Read and Validate AirVisual Data
components.description: Validates and reads the JSON file created by the previous task to ensure data integrity before database loading.

upstream_policy.description: Depends on successful completion of get_airvisual_data_hourly.

components.name: Load AirVisual Data to PostgreSQL
components.description: Transforms JSON data into a dimensional model and loads it into PostgreSQL tables with proper referential integrity.
outputs: Records in dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable

upstream_policy.description: Depends on successful completion of read_data_airvisual.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

output_file_path.description: Path to save the JSON file

temp_file_path.description: Path to save the temporary file during atomic write

input_file_path.description: Path to the JSON file from the previous task
Path to the JSON file from the previous task

pollution_mapping_file_path.description: Path to the pollution mapping file

weather_mapping_file_path.description: Path to the weather mapping file

sources: AirVisual API (http://api.airvisual.com/v2/nearest_city) - Fetches current air quality and weather data using latitude/longitude coordinates.
sinks: PostgreSQL Database (localhost:5432/airvisual_db) - Loads transformed JSON data into dimensional tables (dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable).
